{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> θαῦμα</b>, ατος, τό, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>θῶμα</b> (compare θαυμάζω): (see. θεάομαι): <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> of objects, <b>wonder, marvel</b>, in <i>Epic dialect</i> always in <i>singular</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.99, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; θαῦμ᾽ ἐτέτυκτο πελώριον, of Polyphemus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.190; θαῦμα βροτοῖσι, of a beautiful woman, 11.287 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἄσπετόν τι θ., of Hercules, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 961 (Lyric poetry), etc.: frequently with \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, θ. ἰδέσθαι <b>a wonder</b> to behold, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.725, etc.; θ. ἰδεῖν “hymnus ad Venerem” 205, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 318; θ. ἰδεῖν εὐκοσμίας 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 693; θ. ἀκοῦσαι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 1.26; θ. ἀνέλπιστον μαθεῖν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 673, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; θαῦμ᾽ ὅτι.. <b>strange</b> that.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.2 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; οὐ θαῦμά [ἐστι] no <b>wonder</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 10.50 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so καὶ θ. γ᾽ οὐδέν and no <b>wonder</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 99; τὸ μὴ πείθεσθαι θ. οὐδέν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 498d, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τί τοῦτο θ.; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 439; ἦ μάλα θ. κύων ὅδε κεῖται 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 17.306; θῶμα ποιεῖσθαί τι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.68; τί τινος [prev. author] 9.58 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 7.99; περί τινος [prev. author] 3.23: after 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus in _plural_, θαύματ᾽ ἐμοὶ κλύειν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1166 (variant θραύματ᾽) θαύματ᾽ ἀνθρώποις ὁρᾶν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1142 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; θαυμάτων κρείσσονα or πέρα things more than <b>wondrous</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ba.” 667, “Hec.” 714. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> in <i>plural</i>, also, <b>puppetshow, toy theatre</b>, θ. δεικνύναι, ἐπιδεικνύναι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 514b, “Lg.” 658c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν θ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Characteres” 6.4, compare 27.7, 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.28 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>mountebank-gambols</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 2.1, compare 7.3 (_sing._)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν τοῖς θ. ὑπεκρίνετο μίμους in the <b>jugglers' booths</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 10.452f \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; of menageries, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 15.213 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of mechanical devices, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Mechanica” 848a11: _metaphorically_, ἔνιοι θ. ποιοῦσιν ἐν φιλοσοφίᾳ 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 1.99S. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>singular</i>, <b>puppet</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 644d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>trick</b>, τὸ τῆς σοφιστικῆς δυνάμεως θ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Sph.” 233a. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>wonder, astonishment</b>, θ. μ᾽ ἔχει ὡς.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.326, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἔσχον θ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 897; θ. δ᾽ ὄμμασιν πάρα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 407; θ. μ᾽ ὑπέρχεται 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 928 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μ᾽ ἐλάμβανε θ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 511 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θαύματος ἄξιος worthy of <b>wonder</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 906, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν θώματι εἶναι to be <b>astonished</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.68, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.14 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν θώματι ἔχεσθαι, ἐνέχεσθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.135, 7.128 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν θ. ἐνέχεσθαί τινος <b>at</b> a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 9.37; ἐν θαύματι ποιεῖσθαι 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pompeius” 14; διὰ θαύματος σχεῖν 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 2.2.7: _plural_, θαυμάτων ἐπάξια 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 716, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 967a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2295","accentedUnicode":"θαῦμα","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2296","matchingForm":"θαυμάζω","stepTransliteration":"thaumazō","gloss":"to marvel","_zh_tw_Gloss":"希奇","_es_Gloss":"maravillarse","_zh_Gloss":"希奇"},{"strongNumber":"G2297","matchingForm":"θαυμάσιος","stepTransliteration":"thaumasios","gloss":"marvelous","_zh_tw_Gloss":"奇事","_es_Gloss":"maravilloso","_zh_Gloss":"奇事"}],"shortDef":"wonder, marvel, astonishment","mediumDef":"wonder, marvel, astonishment <br /><b>a wonder; wonder, admiration, astonishment,</b> <ref='2Co.11.14'>2Cor. 11:14;</ref> <ref='Rev.17.6'>Rev. 17:6</ref>*","stepGloss":"marvel","stepTransliteration":"thauma","count":2,"_es_Definition":"una sorpresa, 